
---

### ⚙️ Commands to Set Up Locally

```bash
mkdir sequencing-plus && cd sequencing-plus
git init

# Create directories
mkdir -p data notebooks sequencing_plus tests

# Initialize key files
touch sequencing_plus/__init__.py
touch sequencing_plus/pipeline.py
touch sequencing_plus/metrics.py
touch sequencing_plus/utils.py
touch requirements.txt .gitignore README.md LICENSE

# Recommended gitignore entries
echo -e "data/\n__pycache__/\n*.pyc\n.ipynb_checkpoints/" > .gitignore

# Initialize Git
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit: project structure and boilerplate"
